@renc/global/Drawing.documentation: Drawing is a library used for drawing 2D objects to the screen. Holds the constructor for Drawings.

@renc/global/Drawing.new:
Returns a new Drawing object of the specified class.
```lua
local quad: Drawing.Quad = Drawing.new("Quad")
```
@renc/global/Drawing.Font: An enum of the different font types available to `Drawing.Text`.

@luau/global/debug.documentation: This library provides functions useful for debugging and profiling code.

@renc/global/debug.getupvalue: Returns the value of the upvalue at the given index of the function or level `fn`.
@renc/global/debug.getupvalues: Returns the list of upvalues in the function or level `fn`.
@renc/global/debug.setupvalue: Assigns the value to the upvalue with the given index of the function `fn`. If an existing upvalue was changed, it returns the name of the upvalue.
@renc/global/debug.getconstant: Returns the constant at the given index of the function or level `fn`.
@renc/global/debug.getconstants: Returns the list of constants in the function or level `fn`.
@renc/global/debug.setconstant: Assigns the value to the constant with the given index of the function `fn`.
@renc/global/debug.getproto: Gets the inner function at the given index of the function or level `fn`. If `list` is true, returns a list of garbage collected instances of the function. Otherwise, return a function that is not equivalent to the original function.
@renc/global/debug.getprotos: Returns a list of inner functions for the function or level `fn`. The functions returned will not have upvalues and are not equivalent to the original function.
@renc/global/debug.setstack: Assigns the value to the stack item with the given index of the function `fn`.
@renc/global/debug.getstack: Gets the runtime stack for the level `fn`. If `index` is provided, returns the stack item at the given index.
@renc/global/debug.getinfo: Returns a table with information about the function or level `fn`. The second argument, `options`, is still in progress.
@renc/global/debug.getregistry: Returns the Lua registry table. The registry is a predefined table that can be used by any C code to store whatever Lua values it needs to store.
@renc/global/hookfunction: Redirects attempts to call to `fn` with `hook` and returns the original function.
@renc/global/isrencclosure: Returns whether the closure was created by RENC
@renc/global/iscclosure: Returns whether the closure is a CClosure
@renc/global/islclosure: Returns whether the closure is a LuaClosure
@renc/global/newcclosure: Transforms a LuaClosure into a CClosure with error handling
@renc/global/isrbxactive: Returns whether the Roblox window is active.
@renc/global/mousemoverel: Moves the cursor relative to it's current position.
@renc/global/setscriptable: Flags a property of `instance` as scriptable.
@renc/global/gethiddenproperty: Gets a property of `instance` regardless of the IsScriptable flag.
@renc/global/sethiddenproperty: Sets a property of `instance` to value regardless of the IsScriptable flag.
@renc/global/getproperties: Returns all properties of `instance`, including hidden properties.
@renc/global/getspecialinfo: Gets special properties of certain instances.
@renc/global/fireclickdetector: Sends a click signal for the ClickDetector.
@renc/global/firetouchinterest: Fires the Touched/TouchEnded event of otherPart and part based on touched.
@renc/global/getconnections: Returns a list of connections for the given signal.
@renc/global/getscriptclosure: Creates a LuaClosure for the given script.
@renc/global/decompile: Decompiles a script and returns a representation of the source.
@renc/global/getcallingscript: Gets the script that called the current function.
@renc/global/getloadedmodules: Returns a list of all loaded ModuleScripts.
@renc/global/getscripts: Returns a list of all existing scripts.
@renc/global/rconsolename: Creates a Windows console using the name.
@renc/global/rconsoleprint: Outputs data to the Windows console.
@renc/global/rconsoleinfo: Outputs data to the console preceded with [INFO].
@renc/global/rconsolewarn: Outputs data to the console preceded with [WARNING].
@renc/global/rconsoleerr: Outputs data to the console preceded with [ERROR].
@renc/global/rconsoleclose: Closes the Windows console if it is open.
@renc/global/rconsoleinput: Reads input from the Windows console.
@renc/global/messagebox:
Prompts a MessageBox with the given text, caption and flags, and returns the result.
```lua
MsgBoxResult: number
   | 1: OK
   | 2: CANCEL
   | 3: ABORT
   | 4: RETRY
   | 5: IGNORE
   | 6: YES
   | 7: NO
   | 10: TRYAGAIN
   | 11: CONTINUE
```
@renc/global/request:
Sends an HTTP request using a dictionary to specify the request data, such as the target URL, method, headers and request body data. It returns a dictionary that describes the response data received.
```lua
type RequestOptions = {
	Url: string,
	Method: string?,
	Headers: { [string]: string }?,
	Body: string?,
}

type Response = {
	Success: boolean,
	StatusCode: number,
	StatusMessage: string?,
	Headers: string?,
	Body: string?,
}
```
@renc/global/getrawmetatable: Returns the metatable of the given object. Unlike `getmetatable`, it ignores the `__metatable` metamethod.
@renc/global/setrawmetatable: Sets the metatable for the given object. Unlike `setmetatable`, it ignores the `__metatable` metamethod.
@renc/global/setreadonly: Sets whether a table can be written to. Typically used to temporarily unlock metatables.
@renc/global/isreadonly: Returns whether the table can be written to.
@renc/global/checkcaller: Returns whether the calling thread was created by RENC.
@renc/global/setfflag: Sets the value of fflag to value.
@renc/global/queue_on_teleport: Queues a script to be executed after teleporting.
@renc/global/gethui: Returns a hidden CoreGui instance. Typically used to hide GUI objects from being accessed by the game.
@renc/global/setclipboard: Copies a string to the clipboard.
@renc/global/getgc: Returns a list of garbage-collected functions and tables if included.
@renc/global/getcustomasset: Generates a rbxasset:// [`content`](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/articles/Content) URL for the given asset from RENC's `workspace` directory.
@renc/global/setfpscap: Sets the framerate limit. Passing 0 unlocks the framerate.
@renc/global/isfolder: Returns whether a file at the given path exists and is a folder.
@renc/global/isfile: Returns whether a file at the given path exists and is a file.
@renc/global/makefolder: Makes a folder if the given path is empty. If `path` is a file, it will error.
@renc/global/delfile: Deletes a file at the given path.
@renc/global/delfolder: Deletes a folder at the given path.
@renc/global/listfiles: Returns a list of file paths located in the directory.
@renc/global/writefile: Overwrites an existing file or creates a new file.
@renc/global/appendfile: Appends data to a file's contents or creates a new file.
@renc/global/hookmetamethod:
Hooks the metatable method of the given object with `hook`. Returns a function to call the original metatable method.
Throws an error if there is no metatable or method.
@renc/global/customprint: Prints a string with custom properties.
@renc/global/getdevice: Returns the current player's device in `Enum.Platform.x` format. (returns the x as a string)
@renc/global/join: Joins a game or server using the PlaceId and/or JobId parameter(s).
@renc/global/getinstances: Returns a list of every Roblox instance.
@renc/global/getnilinstances: Returns a list of every instance whose Parent is `nil`.
@renc/global/getcallbackvalue:
Returns the current value of an Instance's callback property.
```lua
-- Example
getcallbackvalue(remoteFunction, "OnServerInvoke")
```
@renc/global/getcallbackmember:
Returns the current value of an Instance's callback property.
```lua
-- Example
getcallbackvalue(remoteFunction, "OnServerInvoke")
```
@renc/global/getplayer: Returns the LocalPlayer or the player of the name defined in the `name` string.
@renc/global/getplayers: Returns a list of all the players in the current game.
@renc/global/runanimation: Runs the animation given on the LocalPlayer or the player defined in the `player` parameter.
@renc/global/getscriptbytecode: Returns the bytecode of the given script.
@renc/global/getscripthash: Returns the hash of the given script (bytecode SHA384).
